## Key Decisions

- **Audience:** CTO/VP Engineering (technical leaders)
- **Tone:** Conversational thought leadership
- **Diagrams:** Mermaid with descriptive captions for future image generation
- **Location:** `modules/executive/agentic-flight/README.md` (standalone, outside numbered modules)
- **No exercises, personas, or story arcs** â€” pure thought piece

## Deliverables

1. **README.md** â€” Long-form thought leadership article (~3500 words) with full narrative, diagrams, and tables. This is the source of truth content.

2. **Slidev deck** (end goal) â€” Convert README.md into `slides/modules/executive-agentic-flight.md` for presentation delivery. Slides will:
   - Extract key points from each section
   - Feature Mermaid diagrams prominently
   - Use the Primary Six and Metaphor Mapping tables as visual anchors
   - Target ~15-20 slides for a 30-minute executive presentation

## Core Message

> "Vibe coding is for hobbyists. Enterprises are litigation targets.
>
> AI agents are autopilotâ€”they multiply what a single developer can deliver. But you can't fly on autopilot without instruments.
>
> Your investment in observability, compliance gates, and quality automation isn't overheadâ€”it's the prerequisite to unlocking agentic productivity. No instruments = no flight clearance.
>
> The organizations that win aren't those with the most developers. They're those whose developers can safely fly the most planes."

## Metaphor Mapping

| Aviation | Enterprise Development |
|----------|----------------------|
| Pilot | Developer |
| Autopilot | AI Agent (Copilot) |
| Instruments | Test/Security/Compliance/Performance dashboards |
| Pre-flight check | Instrumentation & flight plan verification |
| Takeoff | Starting agentic session |
| Cruise | Monitor instruments, steer as necessary |
| Landing | Code complete, attestable, deployment-ready |
| Flight plan | Task scope, acceptance criteria, guardrails |
| ATC | CTO/VP Eng (strategic coordination) |
| Ground crew | Platform/DevOps (maintain instruments) |
| FAA | Security/Compliance (regulatory framework) |
| Turbulence | Incidents, changing requirements, tech debt |
| Multiple aircraft | Concurrent agentic sessions |

